Nigeria will clash with Tunisia in a 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) Round of 16 tie on Sunday night. The 2021 AFCON match between Nigeria and Tunisia will take place at the Roumdé Adjia Stadium, Garoua, in Cameroon. Nigeria had qualified for the 2021 AFCON Round of 16 after beating Egypt, Sudan and Guinea-Bissau in the group stage. Austine Eguavoen’s side tops Group D with 9 points from three games. Recall that Nigeria defeated Tunisia 1-0 in the third-place match of the AFCON 2019 in Egypt, thanks to Odion Ighalo’s early goal. Nigeria’s starting XI: Okoye, Aina, Omeruo, Troost-Ekong, Sanusi, Ndidi, Aribo, Chukwueze, Iheanacho, Simon, Awoniyi Tunisia’s starting XI: Rafia, Jaziri, Msakni, Laidouni, Skhiri, Slimane, Haddadi, Talbi, Ifa, Drager, Ben Said. Full Time: Nigeria 0 – 1 Tunisia (Alex Iwobi, red card, 66) (Youssef Msakni, 47)